<p>Reviewing feature information</p><p>See the information added about the feature and how the feature
	 impacts work packages and change drivers. 
  </p> 
	  
		<ul> 
		   
			 Impacted items must be linked to
				the feature in order to appear in this view. 
			  
		   
		   
			 To edit the information, you
				must have the right permissions. 
			  
		   
		 
	 </ul> 
	  
		<p> A feature can result in several
		  different work packages, raise change drivers, and impact numerous
		  deliverables. CORDAP provides you with a summary view for each feature. This
		  view includes the feature details, and shows all work packages and change
		  drivers linked to the feature. 
		</p> 
	  
	  
		 
		   In 
			 My Products, expand the desired product. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Click the desired release. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Click 
			 Features. 
		   
		  The list of features included in the selected release
			 appears. 
		   
		 
		 
		  (Optional) Click 
			 Display all features to show all features for
			 the product regardless of release. 
		   
		 
		 
		   Click the name for the desired feature. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Review the feature details. 
		   
		   
			 <p>Depending on your permissions,
				you can click on the feature name to edit the details. 
			 </p> 
		   
		 
		  Review the work packages linked to this feature. 
		   
		   
			 <p>Within this area you can sort
				the list of work packages, view the details for the work packages, update the
				work packages, and view unassigned work packages. Depending on your
				permissions, you might also be able to create new work packages that will be
				automatically linked to this feature. 
			 </p> 
		   
		 
		  Review the change drivers linked to this feature. 
		   
		   
			 <p>Depending on your permissions,
				you can click on the change request name to edit the details. 
			 </p> 
		   
		 
		  View the details for another feature by clicking on the current
			 feature's name in the bread crumb above the feature details and then clicking
			 the desired feature's name. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Return to the complete feature list by clicking 
			 Features in the bread crumb above the feature
			 details. 
		   
		 
	  
		<p> Feature information is shown for
		  your review. 
		</p> 
	  
  